# Eris Challenge Creation Format - Master Blueprint
now lets create our challenge using the challenge name as the folder title and the challenges should be inside /workspaces/Ojjagun/erismetete/Challenges

Use this format as your canonical reference when building any new Eris ML challenge. Every section maps directly to a required deliverable. No section is optional.

---

## 0. Platform Submission Workflow - Understand BEFORE You Build

Eris uses a two-phase submission process. Understanding this upfront shapes how you organize your work.

### Phase 1: Upload Dataset

You must upload and get your dataset accepted before you can create a challenge from it.

What you upload to the platform:

- Title: Clear, descriptive name. Format it as Domain or Industry followed by Data Type followed by Purpose. For example, E-Commerce Transaction Fraud Detection Dataset.
- Description: Paste the full content of your DATASET.md. This is the platform description.
- Data Files: Upload only raw dataset files. Do not upload train or test splits. Do not upload scripts.
- License: Must allow commercial use. See the table below.
- Source URL: Original source link for public data, or note Synthetic for generated data.

Supported upload formats: csv, json, parquet, zip, tar.gz, 7z

Archive rules:

- Archives are auto-extracted by the platform.
- Files must be at the root of the archive. No extra parent folder wrapping them.
- BAD: mydata.zip containing mydata/transactions.csv (nested parent folder)
- GOOD: mydata.zip containing transactions.csv (files at root)

The platform runs three validation checks covering file readability, description completeness, and license selection. All must pass before you can submit.

### Phase 2: Create Challenge

Once your dataset is accepted, you create a challenge from it.

What you fill or upload on the platform:

| Platform Field | Source File | Action |
|---------------|-------------|--------|
| Select Dataset | none | Pick your accepted dataset from the dropdown |
| Challenge Title | none | Type it using Domain Context plus Task Type format |
| Problem Description | PROBLEM.md | Paste full content. Markdown renders on platform |
| Prepare Script | prepare.py | Upload file |
| Grading Script | grade.py | Upload file |
| Rubrics | RUBRICS.md | Add each rubric via the platform editor |
| Reference Solution | solution.ipynb | Upload notebook file |

Files that stay local and are not uploaded to the platform:

- generate_dataset.py is used to create the raw data and is not submitted
- run_solution.py and solution.py are script versions. Only solution.ipynb is uploaded
- DATASET.md was already pasted as the dataset description in Phase 1
- The dataset folder contents were already uploaded as raw data in Phase 1

### License Requirements

| License | Acceptable | Notes |
|---------|------------|-------|
| CC0 Public Domain | Yes | Best for synthetic data |
| CC-BY 4.0 | Yes | Requires attribution |
| MIT | Yes | Permissive |
| Apache 2.0 | Yes | Permissive |
| CC-BY-NC | No | Non-commercial. Will be rejected |
| GPL | Risky | May cause issues. Avoid |

Important: On Kaggle and HuggingFace, datasets are often re-uploaded by users who may not have relicensing rights. Always verify the license from the original publisher.

### Tier Limits

| Tier | Pending Reviews | Weekly Submissions | How to Unlock |
|------|----------------|-------------------|---------------|
| New User | 1 | 5 | Default |
| Problem Creator | 3 | 20 | 1 accepted challenge |
| Trusted Creator | Unlimited | Unlimited | 3 accepted challenges |

As a new user, you can only have one challenge pending review at a time. Focus on quality. One accepted challenge unlocks higher limits.

